data.value: Venus’s long, flowing hair is another fascinating aspect of the painting. In classical mythology, hair was often a symbol of beauty, and Botticelli’s depiction of Venus with her locks delicately cascading down her shoulders emphasizes her ethereal beauty. However, many art historians also suggest that Botticelli’s rendering of Venus’s hair was symbolic of purity and divine beauty, further enhancing the spiritual dimensions of the goddess’s character.
